Here is a force-directed graph with forces calculated on the GPU. It's built using three.js and siefkenj's dotgraph parser.

This is a graph of the Leap Motion tracking software's class inheritance structure.

If you have a Leap Motion controller, AND V2 TRACKING navigate through the scene, pinch and move the cameras position with your right hand, and pinch and move the position you are looking at with your left hand. Otherwise click and drag to rotate, and scroll to zoom!

To try out other camera controls ( or build your own ), check out:

  • Leap Three Camera Control Tutorial
  • Leap Three Camera Control Repo
